“member” –
* means a member of the Committee; and
* includes the Chairperson;

“officer” –
* means a public officer appointed under section 14(1); and
* includes â
	* the Director;
	* an enforcement officer;

The Office shall be administered and managed by the Energy Efficiency Committee, which shall consist of –
* a Chairperson, with an engineering background and having experience and knowledge in energy management, to be appointed by the Minister;
* a representative of the Ministry;
* a representative of the Ministry responsible for the subject of environment;
* a representative of the Ministry responsible for the subject of industry;

The Office shall be administered and managed by the Energy Efficiency Committee, which shall consist of –
* a Chairperson, with an engineering background and having experience and knowledge in energy management, to be appointed by the Minister;
* a representative of the Ministry;
* a representative of the Ministry responsible for the subject of environment;
* a representative of the Ministry responsible for the subject of industry;
* a representative of the Ministry responsible for the subject of local government;
* a representative of the Ministry responsible for the subject of public infrastructure, with experience in engineering or architecture;
* a representative of the National Transport Authority;
* a representative of the Joint Economic Council ;
* a representative of the Institution of Engineers;
* a representative of the Mauritius Association of Architects; and
* 2 technical experts, with qualifications and experience in energy efficiency matters, one of whom shall be from the University of Mauritius, to be appointed by the Minister.
* a member of the Assembly;
* a member of a local authority; or
* otherwise actively engaged in politics.
* on the completion of his term of office;
* on his resignation;
* where he becomes a member of the Assembly or local authority, or otherwise actively engaged in politics; or
* where he, without sufficient cause, fails to attend 3 consecutive meetings of the Committee.

A technical committee shall –
* meet as often as may be necessary and at such time and place as the chairperson of the technical committee thinks fit;
* meet as and when required by the Committee.
* be responsible for the execution of the policy of the Office on energy efficiency and conservation;
* be responsible for the control and management of the day-to-day business of the Office;

The Minister may, for the purposes of this Act, make such regulations as he thinks fit.
* for the labelling requirements and specifications for any equipment, machine or appliance which is imported, manufactured or sold in Mauritius;
* for the criteria to classify energy consumers;
* for the minimum qualification standards for certification of energy auditors and related procedures for energy audits;
* for any other matter related to energy efficiency;
* that any person who contravenes them shall commit an offence and shall, on conviction, be liable to a fine not exceeding 100,000 rupees.
